Viewing data

Ive downloaded a small set of data from the International Atomic Energy Agency Global Network for Isotopes in Precipitation that includes water isotope data collected in the last 10 years from 14 sites around the world. With this data source, I cant pull directly, but I can convert and load a .csv. The code chunk that produces this table also cleans up the data for display. The GNIP source doesnt specify units (!!) so I have had to guess.

Getting this to look better will require adjusting the table style in the theme, and messing with kable or another package. Having special characters in a table display would be nice, but since they arent allowed in column names for raw data, it may not be the best precedent to set.

Post plot

A basic ggplot for proof of concept.

theme_set(theme_tufte(base_family = "Helvetica"))

axis.x.label <- expression(paste(delta^{18}, "O ( VSMOW)"))
axis.y.label <- expression(paste(delta, "D ( VSMOW)"))

plot.basic <- ggplot() +
  
  # plot features
  geom_point(data=waters.all, aes(x=O18, y=H2, color=Country)) +
  geom_abline(data=NULL, aes(slope=8, intercept=10, color="GMWL")) +
  
  # legend 
  scale_color_colorblind() + 
    # without any adjustments to the legend, this one is haphazard 
  
  # axes and titles
  coord_cartesian() + 
  labs(x = axis.x.label, 
       y = axis.y.label)

plot(plot.basic)
## Warning: Removed 768 rows containing missing values (geom_point).
